                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul-General <persName type="from">Steinhart</persName> to
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Steinhart acknowledges receipt of cable instructions and states that message
                    in question, together with presence of war vessels, will have greatest influence
                    with Cuban Congress and insurgents in the field. It is reported that President
                    Palma consents to appoint a congressional commission composed of men of both
                    parties, who will modify the electoral and municipal laws as demanded by the
                    insurgents.)</p>
            </div>
